import React,{useState} from "react"
import { Container,Stack,List,ListItem,Flex,Heading } from "@chakra-ui/react"

const App = ()=>{

  const [players, setPlayers] = useState([
    {name:  "Player 1"},
    {name:  "Player 2"},
    {name:  "Player 3"},
    {name:  "Player 4"},
    {name:  "Player 5"}
  ]);

  return (
    <Container maxW="800px">
      <Flex justify="space-between" height="90vh" align="center">
        <Stack width="300px">
          <Heading fontSize="3xl" color="yellow.800" textAlign="center">Players</Heading>
          <List p="4" minH="70vh" boxShadow="xl" borderRadius="md">
            <ListItem>Players</ListItem>
          </List>
        </Stack>
        <Stack width="300px">
          <Heading fontSize="3xl" color="teal.800" textAlign="center">Team</Heading>
          <List p="4" minH="70vh" boxShadow="xl" borderRadius="md">
            <ListItem>Players</ListItem>
          </List>
        </Stack>
      </Flex>
    </Container>
  )
}

export default App
